 COLON IN UDC.IN UDC A LARGE NUMBER OF SYMBOLS ARE USED TO FORM THE COMPLEX NOTATION. MOSTOF THESE SYMBOLS HAVE SEVERAL POSSIBLE MEANINGS WHICH CAUSE PROBLEMS,ESPECIALLY IN THE CASE OF THE COLON, WHEN UDC IS USED IN AN AUTOMATEDINFORMATION SYSTEM. THE COLON IS CLEARLY INTENDED AS A SIGN DENOTING ARELATIONSHIP NEEDING NO FURTHER DEFINITION BETWEEN 2 NUMBERS. THE USE OF THECOLON WITH MORE THAN 2 UDC NUMBERS, ALTHOUGH UNOFFICIAL, HAS BECOMEWIDESPREAD; THE RANGE OF PERMITTED PERMUTATIONS IS DESCRIBED. WHERE THE COLONMAY BE USED BETWEEN 2 NUMBERS, THE POSSIBLE REVERSIBILITY OF THE RELATIONSHIPMAY BE TAKEN FOR GRANTED. IF THE POSSIBILITY OF PERMUTATION IS REMOVED THENTHE COLON RESUMES ITS ORIGINAL FUNCTION OF DENOTING A HIERARCHIC RELATIONSHIPBETWEEN 2 OR MORE UDC NUMBERS